On univariate analysis of the patients with PCNSL (Table 3
), ASCT in CR1 versus not in CR1 was the only statistically significant variable (PFS: HR, 13.36; 95% CI, 1.48-120.18, P = .007; OS: HR, 12.89; 95% CI, 1.43-115.88; P = .008). On univariate analysis of SCNSL/CNS relapse (Table 4
), patient age ≤ 60 years and Karnofsky score < 80 were statistically significant factors for PFS (patient age: HR, 6.55; 95% CI, 0.75-57.22; P = .046; Karnofsky score: HR, 0.17; 95% CI, 0.03-0.94; P = .036) but not for OS (age: HR, 4.22; 95% CI, 0.47-37.84; P = .148; Karnofsky score: HR, 0.22; 95% CI, 0.04-1.32; P = .097).
